{Marlbrook Bridge}is about 3 km. outside Bridgnorth on the{Cleobury- } {Mortimer Road}(B4363). There have been a few crashes at this point because the road is full of twists and turns.In winter it is especially {dangerous}in frosty conditions.
Up the road they are cutting down some{old trees}because they are unsafe. As they want to preserve the wood, they have planted some new trees. The bridge is made out of {marlstone}and it has got two semi- circular{arches.}The road narrows over Marl brook at this point. The banks have been strengthened on the Bridgnorth side. After Cleobury, the road leads to{Ludlow}or{Bewdley. }
